cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language generation and bias reduction, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a BERT-based classifier and encoder-decoder models also suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE). Lastly, the mention of a parallel corpus and human evaluation implies a potential interest in computational social science (cs.CY).
